p: Territory of Washington 3rd Judicial District S.S In the District Court holding terms i in the matter of application of William Fox For a Writ of Habeas Corpus Ordering Granting Writ Upon reading and filing the petition of William Fox, duly signed and verified by him wherby it appears that he is illegally imprisioned and restrained of his liberty by L. V. Wyckoff Sheriff of the county of King at Seattle in the county of King in the Territory of Washington and stating where in the alleged illegality consists from which it appears to me that a writ of Habeas Corpus ought to issue. It is ordered that a writ of Habeas Corpus issue out of and under4 the seal of the District Court for the 3rd Judicial District of Washington Territory holding terms at seattle in King County, directed to the said L. V. Wyckoff Sherriff as aforesaid commandikng him to have the body of the said William Fox before me in my chambers in said Seattle on the 14th day of June A. D. 1878 at 9 o clock a. m. of that day to do and recieve what shall then and there be considered concerning the said William Fox toegether with the time and cause of his detention and have then and there the said writ Dated June 13th 1878 J. R. Lewis Judge
